This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper compares two popular approaches for machine translation: statistical and neural. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the models, which involves training and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses language similarity, which could be related to cs.CY (Computational Linguistics).
